reviews.text: HK style Vietnamese food, very reasonably priced
Not the authentic Vietnamese cuisine but definitely HK-listed food. The 香茅豬扒飯 is really prepared with heart. Also recommending the fake Vietnamese beef noodle and curry calamari.

Claims to serve Vietnamese cuisine but turns out inauthentic. Nevertheless, the food was good to taste. Although the phở was not exactly the Vietnamese one, it was chewy and not soggy. The competitive price reflects the no-frills decor. One thing to keep in mind, don't ask the waitress (elderly lady) about your order, or else she might nag forever 😂
Cheep, chearful and honest food.
Like it. Local food.
